<p align="center"><strong>COMPENSATION  &amp; BENEFITS</strong><br clear="all" />
</p>
<div align="center"></div>
<p><b>1. POLICY STATEMENT:</b></p>
<p><br />
  It is the company's policy to pay to an employee a salary that is both  equitable and competitive.</p>
<p><br />
  <strong>2<u>. GENERAL</u></strong></p>
<ul>
  <li>The overall goal of the Compensation  and Benefits program at PMSL is to attract, retain and motivate a  high-performing workforce.</li>
  <li>HR &amp; Administration Department conducts  annual market survey to ensure that the total compensation program remains  competitive.</li>
  <li>The salary of the employee shall be  determined by the Company and shall be within the company&rsquo;s salary structure.  Employee shall be informed of the salary grade applicable to him/her at the  time of confirmation in service and whenever he/she is promoted.</li>
</ul>
<p><strong>3.<u> SALARY DEFINTIONS:</u></strong></p>
<ul>
  <li>Basic Salary shall mean the Initial Salary  and Cost of Living Allowance (COLA). </li>
  <li>The monthly payment to employee consist  of basic salary in addition to other allowances, which is sum payable to  employee for service with the company and will be paid at the end of the month.</li>
</ul>
<p><strong>4<u>. SALARY OF NEW HIRED EMPLOYEE: </u></strong></p>
<ul>
  <li> The salary at the point of entry shall be  determined by the following factors: </li>
  <li> Salary  grade to be offered to the candidate.</li>
  <li>Relevant working experience (in terms  of years) of the candidate. </li>
  <li>Candidate&rsquo;s present gross income  wherever relevant.</li>
  <li>Level of salary expected by the  candidate.</li>
  <li>Salary levels of existing staff of  similar working experience and level of responsibility.</li>
  <li>Educational and competency  qualifications.</li>
  <li>Market salary level of the job.</li>
  <li>As a general guide :-</li>
  <li>A degree holder with less than two  years &lsquo; relevant working experience shall be   offered appointment on salary grade 20 and paid basic salary in accordance  with the salary structure.</li>
  <li>The salary offered to a prospective  employee may be lower than that of existing staff of similar working experience  and level of responsibility in the company. Exceptions to this rule will be  made when the position to be filled requires a critical skill which is scarce  in the labor market.</li>
</ul>
<div align="center"></div>
<p><strong> 5.<u> SALARY OF AN EMPLOYEE ON PROMOTION</u></strong> </p>
<p><br />
  An employee on the promotion shall be  paid an increment to be determined by the company i.e. 10 % of the mid-point of  the next higher grade or top of quartile 1 of the next higher grade whichever  is higher.</p>
<p><br />
  <strong>6. <u>SALARY ADJUSTMENT</u></strong></p>
<p><br />
  <strong>      </strong>Upward salary adjustments may be  granted to an employee to correct pay anomalies on the following basis:-  </p>
<ul>
  <ul>
    <li>Salary  at the point – of- entry offered to him/her is much lower than the normal level  of the   salary paid to employee of  similar experience and qualification.</li>
  </ul>
</ul>
<p>6 .2To recognize his/her level of  skills, education and competency.</p>
<p><br />
  <strong><u>7.  OVER PAYMENT OF SALARY AND ALLOWANCES </u></strong> </p>
<p><br />
  Overpayment of salary and allowances by  mistake must be recovered from the employee as soon as possible.  </p>
<p><br />
  <strong><u>8. SALARY  ADVANCE</u></strong></p>
<p><br />
  The Company may consider paying an  advance of salary upon request of the employee on the following grounds:-</p>
<ul>
  <li>To make arrangement / preparation for  long term overseas assignment/training.</li>
  <li>For marriage.</li>
  <li>For purpose of performing the Haj.</li>
  <li>For some other justifiable reasons.</li>
  <li> The  maximum salary advance is one month salary.</li>
  <li>The salary advance must be deducted  from employee salary in two months.</li>
</ul>
