<p>1.  <strong><u>POLICY </u>                                                                                                                                         <u></u></strong></p>
<p>It  is the company policy to grant salary increment based on the employee&rsquo;s performance  rating and his/her current salary quartile.  </p>
<p><br />
  2.    <strong><u>ANNUAL  BASE SALARY NCREMENT</u></strong><br />
  <strong><u>Quantum: </u></strong></p>
<ul>
  <ul>
    <li>Performance Rating:<strong></strong></li>
  </ul>
</ul>
<p>Increment  shall be granted based on three (3) performances rating namely:-<strong></strong></p>
<ul>
  <li>Outstanding </li>
  <li>Exceeds  Requirements </li>
  <li>Meets  Requirements.</li>
</ul>
<p>             Or any other rating scales  which may be approved by the company.<br />
  2.2 Quartile of current salary.</p>
<p><br />
  <strong><u>Eligibility  Criteria: </u></strong></p>
<ul>
  <li>Employee must have been rated at least  the performance cut off rate, which is annually determined by the company for  the performance cycle.<strong><u></u></strong></li>
  <li>Employee must have been confirmed in  the permanent service by end of 31 December of year eligible for performance  assessment. <strong><u></u></strong></li>
  <li>Employee with less than 12 months of  service as of 31 December of year eligible for performance assessment will have  an increment affected at his / her anniversary date of joining the company.<strong></strong></li>
</ul>
<p><strong><u>       </u></strong><br />
  <strong><u>3.  ANNIVERSERY AND  ANNUAL INCREMENT  </u></strong></p>
<p><strong>   </strong>         The company will grant an employee the first  increment on the anniversary date of his / her appointment provided that the  employee&rsquo;s work performance during the relevant review period has been  satisfactory.<br />
  The  anniversary increment quantum is based on the prevailing annual increment rates  for the year, subsequent increments will be on the first of January of second  year.</p>
<p><br />
  <strong>   4<u>. INCREMENT FOR EMPLOYEE ON LONG TERM DEVELOPMENT  PROGRAM:</u></strong> </p>
<p><br />
  An employee will be granted an increment based  on his/ her performance and training appraisal.</p>
<p><br />
  <strong>5. <u> EMPLOYEE REACHING THE  MAXIMUM OF SCALE</u></strong></p>
<p><br />
  An employee who has reached the maximum of his/ her salary  grade range will not be paid the increment. However he /she will be paid  performance allowance which is the lump sum of the increment based on his/her  performance rating.<strong>  </strong></p>
<p><strong>                                                        </strong><br />
  <strong><u>6. INCREMENT FOR EMPLOYEE ON PROLONGED ILLNESS.</u></strong></p>
<p><br />
  An employee on  prolonged illness will not be paid increment.   </p>
