<p><strong>1.  <u>POLICY </u> </strong></p>
<p><strong>                                                                                                                                       <u></u></strong><br />
  It  is the company&rsquo;s policy to pay bonus based on overall company&rsquo;s performance  results to confirmed employee as an appreciation of his/her service to the  Company during financial year. </p>
<p><br />
  <strong><u>Definition:</u></strong></p>
<p><br />
  Bonus is payment by company to <u>confirmed</u> employees in recognition of achieving targeted performance results during  financial year. Bonus pay is also used to improve employees&rsquo; morale, motivation  and productivity.   <br />
  At the discretion of the Board of  Directors, PMSL might consider paying its employees annual bonus. This is based  on overall company&rsquo;s performance results during the financial year as well as  affordability. The quantum of the payment depends on employee annual  performance result rating.</p>
<p><br />
  2.  <strong><u>Eligibility  Criteria:</u></strong></p>
<ul>
  <li>  An employee who is confirmed by end of 31  December and eligible to PMS cycle of the year is entitled to full or a  proportional share of the bonus depending on the period of service with the  Company in the financial year.</li>
  <li>  An employee who is attending learning&amp;  development program is also eligible for bonus on condition that he / she is  confirmed in his/ her position on or before 31 December.</li>
  <li> An employee who should receive his/her  anniversary increment or salary adjustment on or before 31 December but has not  received it on the bonus declaration date, shall be paid bonus based on his /  her present basic salary.  Accordingly,  the bonus shall be adjusted when his/ her anniversary increment or salary  adjustment is due.</li>
  <li>  An employee whose employment with the Company  is ceased by way of death or is medically boarded out shall be eligible to  bonus payment proportions to his completed days of the services.</li>
  <li>An employee who retires from his  employment with the Company on or after reaching the age of retirement ( 60 )  in respect of the financial year in which he/she retires , shall be paid bonus  in proportion to that part of the year for which he actually been employed.</li>
</ul>
